			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Don't be too hard on yourself<a name="41545"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 23 04 2:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Really it's all about getting comfortable with your character.  Don't set your expectations too high, learn your abilities and use them at the appropriate time.
<br />

<br />
As bards, in many ways, our class is about reaching certain milestones....
<br />

<br />
Soloing becomes much easier with the 26 fear song when combined with our snare song.
<br />

<br />
Twisting becomes much easier when you set up /stopsong and /cast macros for single clicking songs.
<br />

<br />
Mezzing and swarming become easier when you set up a previous target key.
<br />
Swarming becomes viable with our 39 charm.
<br />

<br />
Kiting becomes easier at 38 when we get our second chant.
<br />

<br />
The list goes on....
<br />

<br />
Patience is your friend as a bard because we have to learn how best to respond to our inherent flexibility.  The beauty of being a bard is enjoying that flexibility....  No two bards have to be alike or played in the same way. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
