				<td colspan="2"><span>In 65 levels and 203 AAs, I have probably earned about 2% of that experience solo.  Maybe 10% as a duo with my roommate who plays a druid.  The rest was in groups and I do not regret a minute of it.  I can single kite pretty much anything but it is slow, boring and requires constant attention to a very repetitive process.  Swarm/AE kiting is even worse in that it is more work, albeit for much greater XP rewards.  But when I solo, it starts to feel less like a game and more like work.  When I am grouped with friends, I'm having fun, cracking jokes, generally playing.  PLAYING.  But it comes down to what you can do - finding good groups is not really something anyone else can help you do.  And whether or not that would make a bard fun for you is something only you can say.  It's a game and if you're not enjoying it, change the way you play or change games.</span></td>
